 Anglo-Norman French prefix <i>fi(t)z</i> ‘son of ’, as for example   Fitzgerald  ,   Fitzroy  , or a transferred use of the surname <i>Fitz</i>, which may be of the same derivation, but applied originally to distinguish a son from a father bearing the same given name, or a local name from Fitz in Shropshire, named with the Old English personal name <i>Fitt</i> + <i>hōh</i> ‘hill spur’."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705188,"age":6,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Lord Henry Fitz Stephens was born in 1218, in Winterbourne, Gloucestershire, England, United Kingdom, his father, John Fitz Stephens I, was 32 and his mother, Susan de Bradeston, was 28. He married Spelly Stephens in 1250, in Winterbourne, Berkshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1250, in Winterbourne, Berkshire, England, at the age of 32, and was buried in England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1218–1250":"1218–1250","1222–1250":"1222–1250","1250–1347":"1250–1347","1186–1274":"1186–1274","1190–1218":"1190–1218","1327":"1327","1190":"1190","1347":"1347","1224":"1224","1222":"1222","1274":"1274","1186":"1186","Aft. 1218":"pärast 1218","1250":"1250","1218":"1218","Winterbourne, Berkshire, England":"Winterbourne, Berkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Winterbourne, Gloucestershire, England":"Winterbourne, Gloucestershire, England"},"fi":{"1218–1250":"1218–1250","1222–1250":"1222–1250","1250–1347":"1250–1347","1186–1274":"1186–1274","1190–1218":"1190–1218","1327":"1327","1190":"1190","1347":"1347","1224":"1224","1222":"1222","1274":"1274","1186":"1186","Aft. 1218":"1218 jälkeen","1250":"1250","1218":"1218","Winterbourne, Berkshire, England":"Winterbourne, Berkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England":"Englanti, Yhdist